
[1]carp

   CARP, v.i. Literally, to snap or catch at, or to pick. Hence, to
   censure, cavil, or find fault, particularly without reason, or
   petulantly; followed by at.

   No, not a tooth or nail to scratch

   And at my actions carp and catch. Herbert.

    CARP, n. A fish, a species of cyprinus, an excellent fish for ponds.
    These fishes breed rapidly, grow to a large size, and live to a great
                                    age.
